HEADWORD: Silentiary
<hw>Si*len"ti*a*ry</hw> <pr>(s⟦isl⟧*l⟦ecr⟧n"sh⟦icr⟧*⟦asl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>silentiarius</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>silenciaire</ets>. See <er>Silence</er>.]</ety> <def>One appointed
to keep silence and order in court; also, one sworn not to divulge
secrets of state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

